</CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Lanys Community Forum</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumenchanter><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Enchanter</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wandering Mind</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumenchanter.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://acinternet.com/lanys/newTopic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; &nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumenchanter.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic><IMG SRC=http://acinternet.com/lanys/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumenchanter.showMessage?topicID=238.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumenchanter.showMessage?topicID=220.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%"><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#10226A><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#10226A><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uenaldar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enaldar</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3/31/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3:32:40 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Recently payed/traded for the 39th spell Wandering Mind, and have yet to found a use for it. Haven't found a easy way to mem. it right before a pull, (being the 3-4 mintue time to mem. it) and  have no room otherwise for it. Anyone have an answer to when this spell is useful at all? Seems to be one of those spells id never buy till i found a reason, like ITU.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3/31/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3:45:05 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">At your level, it might be useful.  At 50+, its only useful for completing your spellbook.<br>
<br>
You will need to dedicate a slot for it, which would be the same slot you will dedicate for Theft of Thought at level 51+.<br>
<br>
If it helps, i will give you my &quot;typical' spell line up in a dungeon with a decent amount of casting mobs :<br>
<br>
1) Theft of Thought ( you would put wandering mind here)<br>
2) Swap / Buff slot ( slow if no shaman defaults here)<br>
3) Root<br>
4) AoE mez ( level 16 one )<br>
5) Color Flux<br>
6) Tashani <br>
7) Dazzle (single target mez)<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Color shift<br>
<br>
So, you would just put wandering mind in place of theft of thought, then cast it on any caster mob your group sees.  if you are not pulling things with caster mobs, the spell is useless.  If you are , it is a little extra mana to be able to afford all those haste buffs your tanks want.<br>
<br>
By the time i got this spell, it is useless for me at my level cause i simply cant fit it in my lineup.  Its 120 mana over 2 minutes or something, where as ToT is 400 mana instantly.<br>
</font><P><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanamandlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanaman D Lin</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11:52:20 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hard for some of us to say since we never had a chance to use it. I'll give you an idea of what getting ToT is like though, and if after using WM for a bit you feel the same way, by all means keep it up.<br>
<br>
Once you hit 51, and get ToT you feel a lot more dynamic.  You're on your feet a lot more moving around and making things happen. If you're not doing constant crowd control, you can throw a good amount of nukes or slow nearly every target you come along as well as keeping a whole range of buffs up. I try to use ToT the instant it comes back up, even if at like 80% mana and just burn some mana down with nukes. Before ToT, as I'm sure you know, it seems you spend most all of your time sitting only to pop up now and then to cast a mez or refresh some buffs.<br>
<br>
I'd use WM for a bit and see if you can feel the same effect. I would think it's not going to make much of a difference, though for the amount of mana it gives back.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>1:57:32 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I would agree that with ToT, if you are fighting in a dungeon with a fair amount of caster mobs, you almost never have to sit again.<br>
<br>
It is a VERY liberating experience, and makes a dedicated spot for this spell almost a necessity.  Since the spells cost less at 39 than they do at 49, i would think you would get a similar feeling.<br>
<br>
Like Tanaman, i cast theft of thought on every caster mob i see.  If i am almost full mana and we are fighting a caster, i will refresh some haste buffs early ( guarenteed to put a little dent in your mana ), then ToT to get the mana back.<br>
<br>
With the lower spell costs, i would think if you were fighting caster mobs a lot in guk or whatever, you would have a similar benifit if you cast it on every caster you see, AND if you continue to get the mana from the mob after it dies like necros do with health and their bond of death line.  Test it out and let us know...<br>
</font><P><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uenaldar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enaldar</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4:31:07 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Been trying it out a lot lately, and have had no real use for it in a full group (they kill the casters first and fast) while in guk. BUT, when im in skyshrine with those mobs, or quad kiting with druids at ry'gor fort, there has been some use. Been casting Wandering Mind on any mystic the druid pulls. I nuke once, druid takes over, and by the end of the fight (pretty quick) WM plus medding gives me the cost of another gravity flux (337 mana). Only use for me so far, and lets me have time to play with the snow bunnies while the druid has to rest.<br>
 </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/3/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:06:58 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Wandering Mind</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">You need to educate your groups in guk that the casters dont need to die first.  That is the biggest switch for tank classes when you hit 51+, is the enchanters have to retrain the tanks that caster mobs dont do anything different from tank mobs, once they are mezzed.<br>
<br>
Tanks are trained to take out the casters ( especially the healer class mobs ) first, because those mobs will heal the others.  Mobs dont heal while they are mezzed however, and once a mob is mezzed it doesnt matter what kind it is ( for a regular group ).<br>
<br>
Tell your tanks that you can get free mana from caster type mobs, and ask them to leave one till last if they get 3 mobs in a pull.  They will have to get used to doing that anyway, and might as well start them off now, rather than later.<br>
<br>
</font><P><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

